$ Oracle Enterprise Manager Cloud Control

Cloud Control is a → development/web based management console for → development/databases/Oracle.

Components of Cloud Control
  • Oracle Management Service (OMS) (A set of J2EE applications)
  • Oracle Management Agents (processes deployed on each monitored host)
  • Oracle Management Repository (basically an Oracle schema)

→ development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN is accessible from the Cloud Control through a set of wizards. In fact, Oracle says that Cloud Control is simpler than RMAN.

It's possible to define a *job schedule* and specify *job parameters*.

